Vice President Mike Pence visited Hope Christian Church in Maryland to discuss the current state of the nation and how to move forward during these challenging times. He expressed condolences for the death of George Floyd and assured that justice will be served. Pence emphasized that there is no tolerance for violence, police brutality, or rioting, and commended law enforcement for their efforts to maintain peace. He also highlighted the administration's initiatives to address inequalities in African American communities, such as record-low unemployment rates, Opportunity Zones, criminal justice reform, and expanding educational opportunities. Pence emphasized the need for healing and unity in the nation, and sought the counsel and insights of religious leaders to achieve this goal. He promised to bring their thoughts and suggestions back to President Trump and the administration. Pence acknowledged the role of faith in the fight for equality in America and expressed confidence that the nation will overcome these challenges with steady leadership and God's grace.